Name: orofaciodigital syndrome I
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by malformations of the face

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome III
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by dysmorphic facies and severe intellectual deficits

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome IV
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by dysmorphic facies

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome V
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by postaxial polydactyly and median cleft of the upper lip and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the DDX59 gene on chromosome 1q32.

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome VII
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by oral

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome VIII
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by tongue lobulation

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome X
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by facial

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome XI
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome IX
Definition: An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by highly arched palate with bifid tongue

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome XVI
Definition: An autosomal recessive non-syndromic intellectual disability that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the RUN and SH3 domain containing 2 gene (RUSC2) on chromosome 9p13.

Name: orofaciodigital syndrome XVII
Definition: An early infantile epileptic encephalopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the NTRK2 gene on chromosome 9q21.
